    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>A large-scale SARS-CoV-2 serosurvey of New Zealand blood donors (n=9806) was conducted at the end of 2020. Seroprevalence, after adjusting for test sensitivity and specificity, was very low (0.1%). This finding is consistent with limited community transmission and provides robust evidence to support New Zealand\u2019 s successful elimination strategy for COVID-19.</jats:p>",
